attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Linux trojan that establishes persistence by creating and enabling an init script at `/etc/init.d/networkd`. It uses both `update-rc.d` and `chkconfig` commands, indicating it targets both Debian-based and RedHat-based systems. It appears to drop payloads masquerading as standard services, such as `/usr/local/bin/daytime` and `/usr/local/bin/chargen`, and includes functionality to kill existing processes with these names. The malware executes these actions via `/bin/sh` and has cleanup routines to remove its components.
